version_description: This version is 99% true to the original studio version. The only doubt I have is about the passage at the end of the verse progression but I think A/C# fits well.
Kinda off jazzy and some crazy chords , but you can have a lot of fun playing this.
This tab is based off the version of Take On Me that plays in Deadpool 2 ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xohx2jFLF8Y ).

version_description: Originally the piano plays the chords and a steady bass line to the beat. Use this as your strumming pattern or find another one that fits your mood. When having three chords a line, the last chord is played twice as long as the first two chords. The chords that lead to the instrumental chorus may be more complex than described here, but they reflect the main idea of that passage.
